S
4
SCENARIO
You are designing an RL agent for your food delivery platform that must decide which
rider to assign to each incoming order. Your team needs to define the core components
of the RL system before implementation begins.
Question: Identify the agent, environment, set of possible actions, and reward signal for this
delivery dispatch RL system. Justify why your chosen reward signal directly encourages efficient
delivery performance rather than unintended shortcut behaviour.


Answer:

Agent:
The AI dispatch system responsible for assigning riders to incoming orders.

Environment:
The food delivery platform, including customers, riders, restaurants, traffic conditions, and weather.

Actions:

Assign Rider A
Assign Rider B
Delay assignment
Reassign an order
Select the best available rider

Reward Signal:
The reward can be based on:

Faster delivery times (+ reward)
Successful on-time deliveries (+ reward)
High customer satisfaction (+ reward)
Reduced delivery cost (+ reward)
Late deliveries (− penalty)
Order cancellations (− penalty)

This reward signal directly encourages efficient delivery performance because it rewards successful and timely deliveries while penalizing delays and poor service. It discourages shortcut behaviors that could negatively affect customer satisfaction or operational efficiency.



