S
6
SCENARIO
You are advising your company on adopting an RL-based system to personalise meal
suggestions for each customer on your platform, similar to how streaming services use
RL to personalise content recommendations.
Question: Describe how Reinforcement Learning has been applied to recommendation systems
in industry. What advantage does an RL-based recommendation system offer over a model
trained once on historical data, particularly for customers whose food preferences change over
time?


Answer:

Reinforcement Learning has been widely used in recommendation systems by companies such as streaming platforms and e-commerce services to personalize recommendations based on user interactions. Instead of relying only on historical data, an RL system continuously learns from user behavior, such as clicks, purchases, ratings, and browsing activity.

For a food delivery platform, an RL-based recommendation system can adapt to changing customer preferences by updating its recommendation strategy whenever new interactions occur. For example, if a customer changes from ordering fast food to healthy meals, the RL agent gradually learns this preference and recommends healthier options.

The main advantage over a model trained once on historical data is that Reinforcement Learning continuously improves through real-time feedback, providing more accurate and personalized recommendations as customer preferences evolve.


